<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-06-13T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-06-13T16:00:00-05:00" n="502" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d502">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">124.51/134a: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Deputy Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Biddle</hi></persName>)<note n="82" xml:id="d502fn82">At this time in Angers.</note>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-06-13T17:00:00-04:00">June
                                        13, 1940—5 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1. The French Government has been informed that when Ambassador
                                Bullitt finds it impossible to communicate with the French
                                Government you are to act temporarily as representative of the
                                United <pb facs="0450" n="441" xml:id="pg_441"/> States near the
                                French Government for the purpose of maintaining communication with
                                that Government. Therefore, when you are informed by the French
                                Government that they are no longer in communication with Ambassador
                                Bullitt you should assume this temporary function. Report
                                immediately when you assume these duties.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>